cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel algorithm that involves learning mappings and transferring distributions, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with camera variations, which is a common issue in multimedia analysis, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
